data.text/html: Predictor Distributions (set mean/SD to match real data)

Model Equation: y = -10.0 + 0.1×x + 0.5×z
Shows the relationship between predictor and outcome. Look for: linear pattern, spread of points around line.
Checks model assumptions. Look for: random scatter around zero (good), patterns/funnel shapes (bad — suggests non-linearity or heteroscedasticity).

Coefficient Interpretation (Continuous Predictors, RAOS Style)

Intercept (β₀ = -10.0): When x=0 and z=0, the predicted y is -10.0. Slope of x (β₁ = 0.1): Holding z constant, a 1-unit increase in x corresponds to a 0.1-unit higher y. z Effect (β₂ = 0.5): Holding x constant, a 1-unit increase in z corresponds to a 0.5-unit higher y. (Currently held at z=100.0 for visualization)
